{"title_page": "Dipika Chikhlia", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Dipika Chikhlia Topiwala\n| image               = Dipika_Chikhlia_Topiwala.png\n| image_size          = \n| caption             = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|4|29}}\n\n| birth_place         = [[Bombay]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| nationality         = [[India]]n\n| office              = [[Member of parliament, Lok Sabha]]\n| term_start          = 1991\n| term_end            = 1996\n| constituency        = [[Vadodara (Lok Sabha constituency)|Baroda]]\n| predecessor         = Prakash Brahmbhatt\n| successor           = Satyajitsinh Gaekwad\n| term_start2         = \n| term_end2           = \n| constituency2       = \n| predecessor2        = \n| successor2          = \n| occupation          = {{hlist|[[Actress]]|[[Politician]]}}\n| spouse              = Hemant Topiwala\n| birth_name          = Dipika Chikhalia\n| source              = http://loksabhaph.nic.in/writereaddata/biodata_1_12/3622.htm\n}}\n'''Dipika Chikhlia Topiwala''' ([[n\u00e9e]] '''Chikhlia'''; born 29 April 1965) is an Indian actress who rose to fame playing Devi [[Sita]] in [[Ramanand Sagar]]'s hit television serial ''[[Ramayan (1987 TV series)|Ramayan]]''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://entertainment.in.msn.com/tv/article.aspx?cp-documentid=3219065 |title=Archived copy |access-date=13 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090915175026/http://entertainment.in.msn.com/tv/article.aspx?cp-documentid=3219065 |archive-date=15 September 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and was known for acting in other Indian historical TV serials. She was also known for her successful debut film ''Sun Meri Laila'' (1983), opposite [[Raj Kiran (Bollywood actor)|Raj Kiran]] and 3 hit Hindi films with [[Rajesh Khanna]], which were ''[[Rupaye Dus Karod]]'', ''[[Ghar Ka Chiraag]]'' and ''[[Khudai]]''. She did one Malayalam film ''[[Ithile Iniyum Varu]]'' (1986), with [[Mammootty]], her Kannada hits were ''[[Hosa Jeevana]]'' (1990), with [[Shankar Nag]] and ''[[Indrajith (1989 film)|Indrajith]]'' (1989), with [[Ambarish]]. She had one Tamil hit film, ''Nangal'' (1992), with [[Prabhu (actor)|Prabhu]], and one Bengali hit film, ''[[Asha O Bhalobasha]]'' (1989), opposite [[Prosenjit Chatterjee]]. She also had acted in few Gujarati movies like Jode Rahejo Raj and Laju Lakhan, opposite  Gujarati Super Star [[Naresh Kanodia]].\n\n==Career==\nDipika made her debut as lead actress in ''Sun Meri Laila'' (1983), opposite [[Raj Kiran (Bollywood actor)|Raj Kiran]], but though her debut film was successful, she did not get A grade films till 1987. Chikhalia was part of the popular television serial ''Dada Daadi Ki Kahani'' in 1985. She meanwhile did supporting roles in hit films like ''Bhagwan Dada'' (1986), ''Kala Dhanda Goray Log'' (1986) and ''Doorie'' (1989) and played lead heroine in the B grade horror  film ''Cheekh'' (1986) and ''Raat Ke Andhere Mein'' (1987), which were box office duds. Later on in (1987), she played the female lead role of [[Sita]] in [[Ramanand Sagar]]'s hit television series ''[[Ramayan (1987 TV series)|Ramayan]]'', which gave her national fame. Before starring in Ramayan, Dipika was the part of Ramanand Sagar's ''[[Vikram Aur Betaal]]''. She continued getting lead roles in hit TV serials like ''The Sword of Tipu Sultan'' and ''Luv Kush'' (both in 1989). Her only hits in Hindi films were ''Ghar Ka Chiraag'' (1989) and ''Rupaye Dus Karod'' (1991), both of which had [[Rajesh Khanna]] in the lead and she had main  roles with more footage in these films. She got more footage in the film ''Khudai'', but the film was a commercial failure in 1994. She played the romantic lead of Rajesh Khanna in two films, ''[[Ghar Ka Chirag]]'' and ''[[Khudai]]''. Her Kannada film as the lead heroine opposite [[Shankar Nag]] was a box office hit in 1990 and her Bengali films ''[[Asha O Bhalobasha]]'' (1989), opposite [[Prosenjit Chatterjee]] and Tamil film ''[[Naangal]]'' (1992) opposite [[Prabhu (actor)|Prabhu]] were box office hits. She also got a supporting role in a Malayalam movie, ''Ithile Iniyum Varu'' (1986), which had [[Mammootty]] in the lead. She met with limited success in Hindi films in the after 1992, as ''Sanam Aap Ki Khatir'' (1992) flopped, which had her in as main lead heroine, she only got supporting roles in Hindi films. \n\nChikhlia followed up her television and film career with a move into politics, riding her fame as a religious icon to an election victory as a Member of Parliament in the Indian [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Vadodara (Lok Sabha constituency)|Baroda constituency]] in 1991 as a [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] candidate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/celebrity/story/remember-deepika-chikhalia-tv-original-sita-ramayan-heres-what-she-doing-now-lifetv-1084346-2017-11-11|title=Remember Deepika Chikhalia, TV's original Sita? Here's what she's doing now|date=2017-11-11|website=India Today|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-12}}</ref> Deepika was also seen in the TV serial ''Chutta Chheda'' (2017) on Colors Gujarati channel. The Gujarati film ''Nattsamrat'' is to be released in August 2018 and she will be seen in her upcoming Hindi movie ''Gaalib'' (2018-2019). Dipika Chikhlia is working again.\n\nShe is now seen in latest movie ''[[Bala (2019 film)|Bala]]'' (November 2019) as Pari's ([[Yami Gautam]]) mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/bala-a-cracker-of-a-film-powered-by-hair-apparent-ayushmann-khurrana/cid/1717854|title=\u2018Bala\u2019: A cracker of a film, powered by \u2018hair\u2019 apparent Ayushmann Khurrana|last=|first=|date=|website=www.telegraphindia.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nChikhlia grew up in Girnar Apartments, in the affluent [[Pali Hill]] area of [[Bandra]], a suburb of  [[Mumbai]].\n\nShe is married to Hemant Topiwala,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://khabridost.in/deepika-chikhalia|title=Deepika Chikhalia|website=khabridost.in|language=en-us|access-date=2018-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180313092937/https://khabridost.in/deepika-chikhalia|archive-date=13 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> owner of Shingar Bindi and Tips and Toes cosmetics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=313168119&capId=79068793&previousCapId=&previousTitle=|title=Hemant Topiwala: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-03-12}}</ref> They have two daughters, Nidhi Topiwala and Juhi Topiwala.<ref>{{cite web  |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOINEW&BaseHref=CAP/2009/09/20&ViewMode=GIF&GZ=T&PageLabel=12&EntityId=Pc01211&AppName=1 |title=Where are they now? Deepika Chikhalia |accessdate=2009-11-21 }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Film !! Language !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1983 || ''Sun Meri Laila'' || [[Hindi cinema|Hindi]] || ||\n|-\n| 1985 || ''Paththar'' || Hindi || ||\n|-\n| 1986 || ''[[Cheekh]]'' || Hindi || ||\n|-\n| 1986 || ''[[Bhagwan Dada (film)|Bhagwaan Dada]]'' || Hindi || Shanti ||\n|-\n| 1986 || ''[[Ghar Sansar]]'' ||Hindi || ||\n|-\n| 1986 || ''[[Ithile Iniyum Varu]]'' || [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] || Priya ||\n|-\n| 1987 || ''Raat Ke Andhere Mein'' || Hindi || Sexy Rosie ||\n|-\n| 1987 || ''Sajanwa Bairi Bhaile Hamar'' || [[Bhojpuri cinema|Bhojpuri]]|| ||\n|-\n| 1989 || ''[[Indrajith (1989 film)|Indrajith]]'' || [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] || ||\n|-\n| 1989 || ''[[Ghar Ka Chiraag]]'' || Hindi || Asha ||\n|-\n| 1989 || ''[[Asha O Bhalobasha]]'' || [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengali]] || Rupa||\n|-\n| 1989 || ''Yamapasam'' || [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] || ||\n|-\n| 1990 || ''[[Hosa Jeevana]]'' || Kannada || Sita as wife of Shankarnag||\n|-\n| 1990 || ''[[Periya Idathu Pillai]]'' || [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] || ||\n|-\n| 1991 || ''Kaala Chakra'' || Kannada || ||\n|-\n| 1991 || ''[[Brahmarshi Vishwamitra]]'' || Telugu ||    ||\n|-\n| 1991 || ''[[Rupaye Dus Karod]]'' || Hindi || Ravi's secretary/Hastinapur Ki Rani ||\n|-\n| 1992 || ''[[Naangal]]'' || Tamil || ||\n|-\n| 1994 || ''[[Khudai]]'' || Hindi || Padmini Raj Anand ||\n|-\n| 1989 || ''Jode Rahejo Raj'' || [[Gujarati cinema|Gujarati]] ||  ||\n|-\n| 1992 || ''Laju Lakhan'' || Gujarati ||  ||\n|-\n| 2018|| ''[[Gaalib]]'' || Hindi ||  ||\n|-\n| 2018|| [[Natsamrat (Gujarati)|''Natsamrat'']] || Gujarati || ||\n|-\n| 2019|| ''[[Bala (2019 film)|Bala]]'' || Hindi ||  Susheela Mishra (Pari's Mother) ||\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://loksabhaph.nic.in/writereaddata/biodata_1_12/3622.htm Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n* {{IMDb name|id=0214355|name=Deepika Chikhalia}}\n* {{facebook|dipikact}}\n* {{Instagram|dipikachikhliatopiwala}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chikhalia, Deepika}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Gujarati people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:10th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Women in Gujarat politics]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Gujarat]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian women politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from Gujarat]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Dipika Chikhlia Topiwala\n| image               = Dipika_Chikhlia_Topiwala.